<TITLE> Huda becomes BNP vice chair </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 26 (bdnews24.com)  In the latest spate of nominations by the BNP chairperson, Nazmul Huda has been made vice chairman and Mir Mohammed Nasir Uddin was made a member of the party's advisory council. A letter undersigned by the party's acting office secretary Rizvi Ahmed on Thursday stated the recent round of nominations by Khaleda Zia under the authority given to her by the party's national council on Dec 8. The appointments were also confirmed by sources at the party's central office. BNP now has 16 vice chairmen and 33 members in the advisory council following these appointments. Khaleda Zia was also given authority to formulate BNP's committee including the standing committee. bdn
